#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn49.35-44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 49 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 49 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:0.2"
msgid "4. Esanāvagga "
msgstr "4. Searches "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:0.3"
msgid "35–44. Esanādisuttadasaka "
msgstr "35–44. Ten Discourses on Searches, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.247, sc1
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.1"
msgid "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, esanā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three searches. "

msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.3"
msgid "Kāmesanā, bhavesanā, brahmacariyesanā—"
msgstr "The search for sensual pleasures, the search for continued existence, and the search for a spiritual path. "

msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.4"
msgid "imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso esanā. "
msgstr "These are the three searches. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.5"
msgid "Imāsaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tissannaṃ esanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "The four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these three searches. "

msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. … "

msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.8"
msgid "uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati. "
msgstr "so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.9"
msgid "Imāsaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tissannaṃ esanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "These four right efforts should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these three searches.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.10"
msgid "(Vitthāretabbaṃ.) "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 45.161–170.) "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.11"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:1.12"
msgid "Esanāvaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:2.1"
msgid "Esanā vidhā āsavo, "
msgstr "Searches, discriminations, defilements, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:2.2"
msgid "Bhavo ca dukkhatā tisso; "
msgstr "states of existence, three kinds of suffering, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:2.3"
msgid "Khilaṃ malañca nīgho ca, "
msgstr "barrenness, stains, and troubles, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.35-44:2.4"
msgid "Vedanā taṇhā tasinā cāti. "
msgstr "feelings, craving, and thirst."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
